6 A Concurrent Resolution authorizing the Oklahoma
House of Representatives or the Oklahoma State Senate
7 to amend or modify legislative deadlines applicable
to the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature
8 pursuant to Joint Rule 7(c).
9
10
11 WHEREAS, pursuant to Rule 7(c) of the Joint Rules of the
12 Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma State Senate, the
13 legislative schedule may be amended or modified by the adoption of a
14 concurrent resolution by a majority vote of the membership of each
15 chamber; and
16 WHEREAS, based on the provisions set forth in Rule 7(c) of the
17 Joint Rules, the legislative schedule previously adopted by the
18 Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma State Senate
19 shall be set aside for the remainder of the 2nd Session of the 60th
20 Oklahoma Legislature.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
22 OF THE 2ND SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
23 CONCURRING THEREIN:
24
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1028 Page 1

1 THAT pursuant to Rule 7(c) of the Joint Rules of the Oklahoma
2 House of Representatives and the Oklahoma State Senate, the
3 legislative schedule previously adopted by the Oklahoma House of
4 Representatives and the Oklahoma State Senate shall, on this date,
5 Wednesday, May 6, 2026, be set aside for the remainder of the 2nd
6 Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
7 Adopted by the House of Representatives the 6th day of May,
2026.
